### -------------------------
### HEALTH & UTILS
### -------------------------

### Health Check (Public)
GET http://localhost:3000/health

### Trigger Error (To test your error handler)
GET http://localhost:3000/crash
x-api-key: granola-123

### Trigger 404 Error
GET http://localhost:3000/this-route-does-not-exist
x-api-key: granola-123

### CORS Preflight (Checks if CORS is working)
OPTIONS http://localhost:3000/api/notes
Origin: http://localhost:5173
Access-Control-Request-Method: GET


### -------------------------
### NOTES (CRUD API)
### NOTE: All these require 'x-api-key: granola-123'
### -------------------------

### 1. Get All Notes
GET http://localhost:3000/api/notes
x-api-key: granola-123

### 1b. Get All Notes (With filters like ownerId)
GET http://localhost:3000/api/notes?ownerId=d0836797-2640-4b89-81fa-a430e2c74c81
x-api-key: granola-123

### 2. Get Note By ID (Replace the ID with a real DB UUID)
GET http://localhost:3000/api/notes/9186beab-2e9a-438e-957f-315c7a800c76
x-api-key: granola-123

### 3. Create a Note 
### IMPORTANT: ownerId MUST be a valid User UUID in your Postgres DB!
### (You may need to manually insert a User in TablePlus/Supabase first to grab an ID)
POST http://localhost:3000/api/notes
Content-Type: application/json
x-api-key: granola-123

{
  "ownerId": "d0836797-2640-4b89-81fa-a430e2c74c81",
  "title": "My Prisma Testing Note",
  "content": "This is successfully writing to the Postgres database!"
}

### 4. Create a Note (Invalid - Missing ownerId)
POST http://localhost:3000/api/notes
Content-Type: application/json
x-api-key: granola-123

{
  "title": "Invalid Note",
  "content": "I forgot the owner id"
}

### 5. Update a Note (Partial Update / PATCH)
PATCH http://localhost:3000/api/notes/f84d82b0-2911-467b-a619-3b46544ae8dd
Content-Type: application/json
x-api-key: granola-123

{
  "title": "Updated Title via PATCH!",
  "content": "Old content was replaced."
}

### 6. Delete a Note
DELETE http://localhost:3000/api/notes/f84d82b0-2911-467b-a619-3b46544ae8dd
x-api-key: granola-123


